LDG_CLOSE(3)                  LDG Call                    LDG_CLOSE(3)

NAME
    ldg_close - close a dynamical library opened by ldg_open()

SYNOPSIS
   #include <ldg.h>

   int ldg_close( LDG *ldg, WORD} *gl);

PARAMETERS
            ldg : LDG descriptor returned by ldg_exec() function.
         global : global array used by AES functions,
         return : 0 if no error or a code error.

DESCRIPTION
   This function removes from the memory a library. The library will be
   really removed if:
        ˙ any client use the library or, 
        ˙ the library is not shareable or.

COMPATIBILITY LDG 1.xx
   ldg_close() replaces ldg_term() and ldg_libterm(). Macros defined in 
   LDG.H emulates these functions.

SEE ALSO
   ldg_open(3), ldg_error(3).
